For {= supplier_channel =}+ distinct Trinidad and Tobago-facing supplier/channel entities for land-security or safety-infrastructure products, identify {= supplier_product_line =}+ meaningful product lines per supplier/channel. For each supplier/product-line pair, cover each of the {= evidence_side =} evidence sides below with a source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL).

The interest is public provenance for real local channels and concrete security products: fencing, gates and gate automation, electric or perimeter fence systems, CCTV/video surveillance, intrusion alarms and sensors, access control, security lighting, and comparable physical or electronic perimeter products.

Evidence sides:
- `local_channel_role`: the page identifies the supplier/channel and visibly ties it to Trinidad and Tobago plus a relevant security, perimeter, or electronic-security product or service role.
- `product_detail_provenance`: the page identifies the product line and contributes source-stated product-line detail beyond a bare category or service label, such as a product/model, brand/OEM relationship, material, durability, specification, warranty, public price, public program, or project detail.

Eligible supplier/channel entities include real suppliers, distributors, installers, marketplace/product channels, official partners, and comparable channels facing Trinidad and Tobago. Product lines should be meaningful product categories, brands, systems, or lines associated with the supplier/channel. A broad label such as "CCTV systems" can count as one product line only when the page frames it as an offered line; additional product lines under the same supplier need a distinct source-framed function, application, construction, brand/OEM series, category, or system. Changing only SKU, size, rating, price, quote status, stock status, contact destination, or near-duplicate catalog-card detail is not a meaningful second product line. Broad directories, contact-only pages, RFQ pages, procurement advice, rankings, foreign geo-SEO pages, and property-security recommendations are out of scope unless the cited page itself earns the active evidence side. Thin local directories or listings can support `local_channel_role` only when visible listing content names the supplier/channel, T&T tie, and in-scope role; they remain weak for `product_detail_provenance` unless real product-line detail is visible.

A single source can cover both evidence sides for a supplier/product-line pair only when the page visibly carries a local-channel anchor and separate concrete product-line detail; a repeated homepage, category page, or listing with only broad service labels does not earn both sides by repetition.

Requirements:
- The page must clearly identify or strongly anchor the named `supplier_channel`.
- The page must anchor the named `product_line` at the bar required by `evidence_side`: for `local_channel_role`, the supplier/channel role may match or encompass the named product line through an in-scope product or service role; for `product_detail_provenance`, the page must identify the named product line, category, brand, system, or line itself.
- The page should make its evidence-side source role visible. For `local_channel_role`, it should show a Trinidad and Tobago-facing supplier/channel role through cues such as local address or coverage, T&T country framing, official company/service context, local directory/listing content that names the supplier and role, supplier/distributor/installer language, or comparable page-visible anchors. For `product_detail_provenance`, it should read as a dedicated product page, product-category page, catalog/PDF, marketplace product listing, OEM/partner page, public program/project source, or comparable page that can carry source-stated product-line detail.
- The page must contribute the active evidence-side substance. For `local_channel_role`, it must visibly tie the supplier/channel to Trinidad and Tobago plus a relevant security, perimeter, or electronic-security product or service role. For `product_detail_provenance`, it must source-state a concrete product/model, category with detail, brand, OEM/authorization, material, durability, specification, warranty, public price, public program, project, or comparable provenance/detail tied to the product line; a bare service/category label is not enough.
- Product-detail, durability, suitability, authorization, public price, public-program, rebate, or source-role claims should be page-stated rather than inferred from product category, supplier type, local climate, or general knowledge.
